        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:32AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 632 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ethelsville, or 9 miles southwest of Millport, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Reform, Millport, Kennedy, Ethelsville, North Pickens Airport,
McShan, Forest, Macedonia, and Shaw.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
